flowchart LR
    subgraph Client[React Client]
        Student[Student Browser\nExam UI + Camera Capture]
        Proctor[Proctor/Admin Browser\nMonitoring Dashboard]
    end

    subgraph Backend[Node.js Backend]
        REST[Express REST API\nAuth + Exam + Answer + Score + Dispute APIs]
        WS[WebSocket Layer\nSocket.IO / WebRTC Signaling]
        Worker[Frame Analysis Worker\nRule-based or ML placeholder]
    end

    subgraph Data[Databases]
        PG[(PostgreSQL\nusers, exams, questions, answers, scores, disputes)]
        Mongo[(MongoDB\nVideoSession, FrameAnalysis)]
        Redis[(Redis / Memurai\nsessions, locks, live flags, pub/sub)]
    end

    Student -->|REST: login, fetch exam, submit answers| REST
    Student -->|WebSocket/WebRTC: live proctoring events| WS
    Proctor -->|REST: reports, disputes, scores| REST
    Proctor -->|WebSocket: live alerts dashboard| WS

    REST -->|SQL queries and ACID transactions| PG
    REST -->|create/read session metadata| Mongo
    REST -->|sessions, rate limits, submit locks| Redis

    WS -->|presence, pub/sub, latest state| Redis
    WS -->|store session metadata| Mongo
    Worker -->|read frame events| WS
    Worker -->|save analysis result| Mongo
    Worker -->|publish suspicious alert| Redis
    Redis -->|push alerts| WS
